<br>
It took bards to get this group to this point, but now they arent really super necessary.<br>
<br>
We have been at this point before.  Increases in stat, resist,  and AC caps smoothed it over.  Well that and overhaste...like the evaj line ...lol.<br>
<br>
Raising caps across the board, adding in % spell mitigation with resists in a song, adding in % damage mitigation with AC buff in a song will help solve this problem, without giving soloers any power.<br>
<br>
Bard stacking on raids beyond 2-3 has been a problem off and on throughout eq.  Its no different than alot of other classes, I just kind of accept it and move on.  You want to be a star, be in a guild with 1-2 bards, you want to feel marginalized be in a guild with 6-8 bards.<br>
<br>
I only see this as a problem in the highest end of the game.  It will eventually be a pervasive problem for all bards if it isnt addressed.  If caps arent raised, you can imagine the gear and stat items and 5 more levels will make alot more bards feel the heat.<br>
<br>
I think we will be ok when OOW comes out, Im not particularly worried about it.  The people on the cutting edge may have to suffer a bit until then.  <br>
 <br>
rack<br>
