 So, tellin me a druid can't keep a place in a CH wheel then? Spam heals from healing classes wont hold up against tvexu? Would think nothing less than a 11-12k tank of whatever class at that level? <br>
Tell me a pally, shaman and druid can't heal as well as a single cleric and I would truly be surprised. And yes, up to GoD you can have a raid with no clerics, rezzing sucks but it can and has been done. I didn't say some classes cannot do stuff more efficiently than others, thats their strength. Curous though... Someone out there has never had a pally/sk tank Quarm? Maybe not to start with(after all, it is a warriors strongpoint), but that got the job done? Would be surprised. Bards are meant to be a fill in the gap type of class, as I said before. My point still stands, and consider back when LDoN came out. most folks wouldn't consider going into a hard LDoN without a cleric...<br>
Talidd, as you pointed out, may be possible going ahead in gear an expansion and killing the expansion before material with less than optimum groups? It's my point, exactly.  Clerics have a role, bards have a role, our role is and always has been utility, not being a one trick pony on a raid. Like a buff bot.<br>
Some expansions, some classes get to shine better than others, according to some end-end game folks, it isn't bards. So what? I can still be good at my job, and still be a benefit. Ok, so my buffs are useless at a certain point according to Racket, could be... Gotta find other stuff to do then that is of some use.. Hmm, HoS/slow incoming, mez adds faster than the chanters, pull if I get the opportunity to or want to, add a nice DS to help tank maintain aggro..etc. I guess I just refuse to feel inferior because I don't do any one thing as well as any class that has it as a specialty. Guess I will see what it's like in time in GoD high end, and I know I will find a way to be useful there, too. I am sorry for those of you that don't. <br>
Also, I am not saying that we shouldn't get songs that make us be of even more use, but I imagine I will always feel useful. I am too versatile not to. At least as much as that 4th shammy is... If only a warrior can tank in high end GoD raids, what are the SK's doing? Pallies can cure and heal at least, what about them? We as Bards have just been spolied for a long long time. I liked it, don't get me wrong.<br>
When I feel I have no use, and stop having fun, I will stop playing, after all it's just a game. <br>
